  "prompt": "How does international law intersect with national laws on money laundering?",
  "response": "International law and national laws on money laundering intersect in several important ways:\n\n1. International Conventions and Agreements\n- UN Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Bilateral and multilateral treaties establishing legal frameworks\n\n2. Harmonization of Legal Standards\n- Standardizing definitions of money laundering\n- Creating consistent reporting and compliance requirements\n- Establishing common mechanisms for investigation and prosecution\n\n3. Mutual Legal Assistance\n- Cross-border information sharing\n- Collaborative investigations\n- Extradition mechanisms\n- Asset seizure and recovery procedures\n\n4. Regulatory Compliance\n- Banks and financial institutions required to implement anti-money laundering (AML) protocols\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- International financial tracking systems\n\n5. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- International cooperation in investigating financial crimes\n- Sanctions against non-compliant jurisdictions\n- Coordinated legal actions across national boundaries\n\n6. Technological Adaptations\n- Addressing emerging challenges like cryptocurrency\n- Developing transnational digital forensic capabilities\n- Creating adaptive legal frameworks\n\nThese intersections create complex but increasingly sophisticated global approaches to combating financial crime.",
